title: Louis Armstrong - And His All Stars & On The Road (1950's)
description:
TWO LASERLIGHT LOUIS ARMSTRONG CDs RECORDED LIVE PROBABLY IN THE FIFTIES (scans included)

*****************************************************************

Louis Armstrong - LOUIS ARMSTRONG AND HIS ALL-STARS

1. High Society (Walter Melrose-Porter Steele)
2. Back O'Town Blues (Louis Armstrong-Luis Russell)
3. C Jam Blues (Duke Ellington)
4. Boogie Woogie On St. Louis Blues (W. C. Handy)
5. Panama
6. Fine And Dandy (Paul James-Kay Swift)
7. Blue Skies (Irving Berlin)
8. Don't Fence Me In (Cole Porter)
9. Lover (Lorenz Hart-Richard Rogers)
10. Whispering (Schonberger-Coburn-Rose)
11. A Song Was Born (Don Raye-Gene DePaul)
12. Mahogany Hall Stomp (Spencer Williams)
13. Ain't Misbehavin' (Razaf-Brookes-Waller)
14. Jack-Armstrong Blues (Louis Armstrong-Jack Teagarden)

All Star Personnel:
Louis Armstrong - trumpet, vocals
Earl Fatha Hines - piano
Jack Teagarden - trombone
Barney Bigard - clarinet
Big Sid Catlett - drums
Arvell Shaw - bass
Velma Middleton - vocals

No recording dates or location listed (I guess early fifties broadcasts)

1992 Laserlight Digital

*****************************************************************

Louis Armstrong - ON THE ROAD

1. I Love Jazz (Sydney Shaw)
2. High Society (Walter Melrose-Porter Steele)
3. Ole Miss Blues (W.C. Handy)
4. Blue Moon (Lorenz Hart-Richard Hart)
5. Sweet Georgia Brown (Ben Bernie-Macei Pinkard-Ken Casey)
6. Blues
7. Mack The Knife (Kurt Weill-Berthold Brecht-Marc Blitzstein)
8. Tenderly (Jack Lawrence-Walter Gross)
9. You'll Never Walk Alone (Oscar Hammerstein-Richard Rodgers)
10. Baby, It's Cold Outside (Frank Loesser)
11. When It's Sleepy Time Down South (Leon & Otis Rene-Clarence Muse)
12. Mahogany Hall Stomp (Spencer Williams)
13. C'est Si Bon (Jerry Seelen-Henri Betti)
14. La Vie En Rose (Mack David-Edith Piaf-Louiguy)

Personnel:
Louis Armstrong - trumpet & vocals
Edmond Hall - clarinet
Trummy Young - trombone & vocals
Squire Gersh - bass
Barrett Deems - drums
Velma Middleton - vocals

No recording date or location listed (I think NYC around 1956 beacause they mention the movie High Society and the Cotton Club)

1992 Laserlight Digital
